WEBVTT

00:02.570 --> 00:06.005
(dog barking in distance)

00:11.112 --> 00:13.312
(suspenseful violin music)
- [ed] hello?

00:13.414 --> 00:14.246
Oh my god.

00:15.383 --> 00:19.852
(suspenseful violin music)

00:19.954 --> 00:22.087
- [operator] 9-1-1,
what's your emergency?

00:22.189 --> 00:23.022
- [ed] it's my wife.

00:23.124 --> 00:26.759
She's gone and everything's...

00:26.861 --> 00:27.726
Oh my god.

00:27.828 --> 00:29.061
- [operator] sir?

00:29.163 --> 00:31.163
Sir, can you explain
to me what's happening?

00:31.265 --> 00:34.333
- [ed] I don't know
what's happened.

00:34.435 --> 00:36.468
There's blood everywhere.

00:37.571 --> 00:39.204
And she's not here.

00:40.641 --> 00:43.442
- [operator] I'm sending
them out right away.

00:43.544 --> 00:44.910
- She's not here.

00:46.981 --> 00:48.313
My wife's not here.

00:48.416 --> 00:51.216
(mysterious music)

01:04.632 --> 01:08.534
okay well, can you

01:08.836 --> 01:10.369
give that one to mommy?

01:11.205 --> 01:12.137
- Thank you.

01:12.239 --> 01:13.138
- [kayla] you're welcome.

01:13.240 --> 01:14.239
- You wanna taste it?

01:14.341 --> 01:15.207
Just a little bit?

01:15.309 --> 01:16.008
- No.

01:16.110 --> 01:16.942
- Okay, okay, okay.

01:17.044 --> 01:18.143
Cereal it is.

01:19.146 --> 01:20.579
- Come here.

01:20.681 --> 01:21.580
There we go.

01:21.682 --> 01:22.815
- You have surgery today?

01:22.917 --> 01:26.085
- Yeah, just one
with my new interns.

01:26.187 --> 01:28.020
Did you have any
luck with the sitter?

01:28.122 --> 01:29.154
- No.

01:29.256 --> 01:30.589
My sister said
that she'll do it,

01:30.691 --> 01:32.891
so I figured I'd bring her
back here after we go shopping.

01:32.993 --> 01:34.359
- [kayla] aunt leigh?

01:34.462 --> 01:35.928
- Yes, auntie leigh.

01:36.030 --> 01:37.262
And she can't wait to see you.

01:37.364 --> 01:39.331
- Kayla, I will see
you after school, okay?

01:39.433 --> 01:40.165
- Okay.

01:40.267 --> 01:40.999
- See you.

01:41.102 --> 01:41.800
- Have a good day.

01:41.902 --> 01:42.734
- You too.

01:44.271 --> 01:46.939
(sirens ring)

01:47.041 --> 01:47.973
- [ed] there it is.

01:48.075 --> 01:50.242
The privilege of every
heart surgeon,

01:50.344 --> 01:51.844
to be able to hold the
lives of our patients

01:51.946 --> 01:53.612
in our very hands,

01:53.714 --> 01:56.582
to have the opportunity
to be either a savior

01:56.684 --> 01:57.649
or a failure.

01:59.086 --> 02:01.920
That's why this opportunity
should not be taken lightly.

02:02.022 --> 02:03.355
And why mistakes

02:03.457 --> 02:05.924
are never an option.

02:06.026 --> 02:06.992
Understood?.

02:08.129 --> 02:08.994
Good.

02:10.397 --> 02:12.030
Let's save a life.

02:12.133 --> 02:15.267
(inspirational music)

02:19.173 --> 02:20.672
- [woman] maybe he has a 1
o'clock appointment

02:20.774 --> 02:21.573
available for me?

02:21.675 --> 02:23.475
- All right.

02:25.479 --> 02:26.812
- Good morning.

02:26.914 --> 02:28.247
- Hey.
- You're here early.

02:28.349 --> 02:30.215
- Did you get the
revised designs?

02:30.317 --> 02:34.219
- I actually was getting ready
to look at them right now.

02:34.321 --> 02:35.654
- Remember this?

02:37.291 --> 02:38.524
Client just called.

02:38.626 --> 02:40.125
Said it's been the
most successful

02:40.227 --> 02:42.828
product launch in their
company's history.

02:42.930 --> 02:46.899
Another reason why your award
tonight is so well-deserved.

02:47.001 --> 02:47.833
- Aw.

02:48.969 --> 02:49.801
I love it.

02:50.938 --> 02:52.271
We can pop it open
during lunch today

02:52.373 --> 02:53.505
and everyone could have a drink.

02:53.607 --> 02:55.340
- Oh no, that's yours.

02:56.277 --> 02:58.210
This is all your genius.

03:00.247 --> 03:03.215
But, I'll see you tonight then.

03:03.317 --> 03:04.750
Maybe we'll raise a glass then?

03:04.852 --> 03:05.851
- Of course.

03:05.953 --> 03:08.487
(light guitar music)

03:08.589 --> 03:10.389
- [ed] I feel better already.

03:10.491 --> 03:11.690
Thank you, doctor.

03:11.792 --> 03:12.858
- You're welcome.

03:12.960 --> 03:15.861
I'm gonna give you
your temperature.

03:17.364 --> 03:18.330
- What it say?

03:18.432 --> 03:19.164
- 100.

03:19.266 --> 03:20.098
- [ed] 100?

03:20.201 --> 03:21.600
Well, that's more like you.

03:21.702 --> 03:23.235
- Well, I have a
waitressing interview.

03:23.337 --> 03:24.503
Yes.

03:24.605 --> 03:26.772
And I have another one
at that hotel on fifth?

03:26.874 --> 03:27.906
As a front desk clerk.

03:28.008 --> 03:29.174
Don't make a big deal.

03:29.276 --> 03:30.342
- But see, that's
a good thing why we

03:30.444 --> 03:31.777
run out and got
you these clothes.

03:31.879 --> 03:32.945
- Yeah, yeah, yeah.
- [ed] do I need more medicine?

03:33.047 --> 03:35.347
- Wait a minute, what
is going on in here?

03:35.449 --> 03:36.348
(man chuckles)
hi!

03:36.450 --> 03:37.783
- Aunt leigh!

03:37.885 --> 03:38.684
- Hi!

03:40.454 --> 03:41.353
Hi baby girl!

03:41.455 --> 03:42.321
- Hi!

03:42.423 --> 03:43.121
- Hey!

03:43.224 --> 03:43.956
- [ed] hey.

03:44.058 --> 03:44.890
- So what's going on?

03:44.992 --> 03:46.358
- We're giving daddy a check-up.

03:46.460 --> 03:47.693
- I got an idea.

03:47.795 --> 03:49.895
How 'bout you pack all
of this up for my place

03:49.997 --> 03:52.698
so these two can get ready
for mommy's big night?

03:52.800 --> 03:53.498
Yeah?

03:53.601 --> 03:54.299
(giggles)

03:54.401 --> 03:55.634
- [leigh] yeah, let's do it!

03:55.736 --> 03:57.603
Ed, you have to see
this dress she just got.

03:57.705 --> 03:59.004
It is smoking.

03:59.106 --> 04:00.606
Come on, come on, come on.

04:00.708 --> 04:02.040
She's so modest.

04:03.143 --> 04:04.843
Smoking, right?

04:04.945 --> 04:06.278
- Wow.
- [leigh] yeah.

04:06.380 --> 04:07.913
I thought it was you
doing the shopping.

04:08.015 --> 04:09.514
- See, that's
exactly what I said.

04:09.617 --> 04:11.984
- Well, you had to wear a
hand-me-down to your graduation.

04:12.086 --> 04:13.719
And look, I know you
dreamed of wearing a dress

04:13.821 --> 04:15.520
like this for your
valedictorian speech,

04:15.623 --> 04:17.623
so you owed it to your 18
year old self to buy it.

04:17.725 --> 04:19.258
Don't be so hard on yourself.

04:19.360 --> 04:22.027
But trust me, once you see
her in it, you will thank me.

04:22.129 --> 04:23.962
- Jade, I didn't know
you were valedictorian.

04:24.064 --> 04:25.097
- [leigh] of course she was.

04:25.199 --> 04:26.064
Come on, little one.

04:26.166 --> 04:26.865
- Wait.

04:26.967 --> 04:27.699
There we go.

04:27.801 --> 04:29.067
Goodbye doctor.

04:29.169 --> 04:30.936
- Have fun with your tt.

04:31.038 --> 04:32.004
- Thank you.

04:32.106 --> 04:32.971
- Love you.

04:33.073 --> 04:33.972
I'll see you later, ed.

04:34.074 --> 04:34.806
- See you.
- See you later, sis.

04:34.908 --> 04:36.541
- Wait, wait, wait!

04:38.812 --> 04:39.978
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

04:42.683 --> 04:45.317
- Guess I'd better go get ready.

04:50.457 --> 04:53.225
(mysterious music)

04:55.029 --> 04:57.496
(bright music)

04:57.598 --> 05:07.306
♪♪

05:25.926 --> 05:28.760
(suspenseful music)

05:28.862 --> 05:38.570
♪♪

05:44.912 --> 05:45.777
- too bad.

05:46.980 --> 05:49.915
(suspenseful music)

05:56.523 --> 05:58.357
- I'll just um...

05:58.459 --> 06:01.493
I'll wear my
anniversary dress.

06:01.595 --> 06:02.461
- Good.

06:04.465 --> 06:07.799
This would've made
you look like a whore.

06:13.907 --> 06:16.708
(suspenseful music)

06:16.810 --> 06:25.183
♪♪

06:25.285 --> 06:28.787
- where is your hard
earned award going?

06:28.889 --> 06:29.821
The mantle?

06:30.591 --> 06:31.556
The office?

06:32.359 --> 06:33.058
The bedroom?

06:33.160 --> 06:34.493
(laughs)

06:34.595 --> 06:37.629
- I don't know yet.

06:37.731 --> 06:40.866
- Well, you gotta show it
off because what can I say,

06:40.968 --> 06:43.301
this one is brilliant.

06:43.404 --> 06:46.671
Always two steps ahead
of everyone else.

06:46.774 --> 06:48.006
- Thank you.

06:48.108 --> 06:50.275
It's not like I'm saving lives.

06:50.377 --> 06:51.843
(woman chuckles)

06:51.945 --> 06:54.813
- that reminds me, my doc says
I may have a little murmur.

06:54.915 --> 06:56.882
Any chance I could
get a second opinion

06:56.984 --> 06:58.650
from the best heart guy in town?

06:58.752 --> 06:59.484
- Rob.

06:59.586 --> 07:00.919
Leave the man alone.

07:01.021 --> 07:02.587
- I'd be happy to.

07:02.689 --> 07:07.959
- Then here, a toast to
my heart and to jade.

07:08.395 --> 07:10.629
Preception's most
creative and outstanding

07:10.731 --> 07:12.597
leader of the year.

07:12.699 --> 07:13.365
- Sorry.

07:13.467 --> 07:14.699
Never touched the stuff.

07:14.802 --> 07:16.768
- [rob] come on,
it's the after party.

07:16.870 --> 07:18.770
- [ed] gotta keep
the hand steady.

07:18.872 --> 07:20.205
- Well, not me.

07:20.307 --> 07:21.673
In fact, I'm gonna see
about getting another bottle

07:21.775 --> 07:23.442
so we can all toast.

07:29.049 --> 07:30.215
- What an ass.

07:31.318 --> 07:34.119
I don't know how you can
stand to work for him.

07:34.221 --> 07:37.389
You and I have a
special day coming up.

07:39.092 --> 07:40.625
- That's right.

07:40.727 --> 07:41.593
10 years.

07:43.130 --> 07:45.464
- Would you like to
celebrate it like last year,

07:45.566 --> 07:48.533
at chateau briond at alouette?

07:48.635 --> 07:52.103
- Well, it's your
favorite, so of course.

07:52.206 --> 07:55.540
- Before we crack this
one, jade, a few words?

07:55.642 --> 07:56.975
- No.

07:57.077 --> 07:58.743
I already gave my long-winded
speech at the ceremony.

07:58.846 --> 08:00.078
(guests protest)

08:00.180 --> 08:01.680
- we want more!

08:01.782 --> 08:02.781
- We want more!

08:02.883 --> 08:05.417
- Okay, all right,
all right, all right!

08:05.519 --> 08:09.421
Well first, my team has
to come up here with me.

08:11.058 --> 08:12.190
Wow.

08:12.292 --> 08:15.293
This award may
have my name on it,

08:15.395 --> 08:16.895
but everybody knows
that marketing

08:16.997 --> 08:18.964
is a collaborative effort,

08:19.066 --> 08:21.433
so if I could put
your names on it

08:21.535 --> 08:23.235
or if could split it into three,

08:23.337 --> 08:27.606
I would because I can't do
what I do without you guys.

08:27.708 --> 08:29.074
- Well said.
- To jade, yes?

08:29.176 --> 08:30.242
To jade!

08:30.344 --> 08:32.878
(guests cheer)

08:34.047 --> 08:35.881
- you're the best.

08:35.983 --> 08:37.616
- Thank you.

08:37.718 --> 08:39.050
Thank you.

08:39.152 --> 08:41.486
(cheers and applause)

08:41.588 --> 08:44.289
oh, exactly.

08:44.391 --> 08:46.191
Absolutely.
Thanks guys.

08:46.293 --> 08:47.859
- Okay, love you too.

08:53.667 --> 08:57.102
It looks like leigh
and kay had a good time.

08:59.473 --> 09:01.606
- Hey look, in the future,

09:01.708 --> 09:03.108
I want someone else
to look after kayla.

09:03.210 --> 09:04.976
- But ed, she's good.

09:06.146 --> 09:08.113
- Jade, don't be naive.

09:08.215 --> 09:09.214
Your sister's been
back in your life

09:09.316 --> 09:10.549
for a few months and bipolar's

09:10.651 --> 09:14.085
hard to manage, even
with meds, all right?

09:19.159 --> 09:20.759
- Yeah, okay.

09:20.861 --> 09:23.795
(mysterious music)

09:34.441 --> 09:36.575
- you seem to give that

09:37.377 --> 09:39.678
liam, quite a lot of
credit tonight.

09:39.780 --> 09:41.112
- Oh, he's just
part of the team.

09:41.214 --> 09:43.648
I gave them both credit.

09:43.750 --> 09:47.586
- Then why couldn't he wait
to get his hands on you?

09:47.688 --> 09:49.554
And you just let him.

09:49.656 --> 09:51.790
Jade, it was humiliating.

09:54.695 --> 09:58.129
- It's just work
colleague, you know?

09:58.231 --> 09:59.064
Liam, jen.

10:00.500 --> 10:03.168
(foreboding music)

10:03.270 --> 10:04.970
- you think he's better
than me, don't you?

10:05.072 --> 10:05.904
- No!

10:06.006 --> 10:08.073
- Just tell me the truth.

10:08.175 --> 10:09.007
You think I'm stupid?

10:09.109 --> 10:10.175
- No!

10:10.277 --> 10:11.109
- You thought I
don't know why you

10:11.211 --> 10:12.277
begged me to go back to work!

10:12.379 --> 10:14.379
- I just needed to work.

10:15.215 --> 10:16.848
It helps me.

10:16.950 --> 10:18.249
- Here we go.

10:18.352 --> 10:20.485
That's right, poor,
depressed jade.

10:20.587 --> 10:21.853
You don't seem to remember that

10:21.955 --> 10:23.922
I'm the one who was
there looking after you

10:24.024 --> 10:25.223
when you had nothing!

10:25.325 --> 10:26.191
No one!

10:27.094 --> 10:28.393
- I'm sorry, ed.

10:30.030 --> 10:31.696
- You're sorry?

10:31.798 --> 10:33.965
What are you sorry for, huh?

10:34.067 --> 10:34.933
- What are you doing?
- I'm sorry.

10:35.035 --> 10:35.734
- No, no, no!
- Tell me!

10:35.836 --> 10:36.735
- What did you do?

10:36.837 --> 10:37.836
What do you do?

10:37.938 --> 10:38.970
What do you do?

10:39.072 --> 10:40.605
Just tell me what you did!

10:40.707 --> 10:41.773
Tell me!

10:41.875 --> 10:42.674
- Please, please!
- What did you do?

10:42.776 --> 10:45.276
(glass breaks)

10:48.448 --> 10:50.248
- you thankless bitch!

10:51.218 --> 10:52.884
Without me, you'd be dead.

10:52.986 --> 10:57.389
(thud)
(jade groans)

11:00.961 --> 11:02.894
I saved you, jade.

11:03.697 --> 11:05.196
Never forget that.

11:07.167 --> 11:09.768
(jade gasping)

11:14.841 --> 11:17.375
(jade crying)

11:21.048 --> 11:21.913
- [eds voice echoing]
I saved you.

11:22.015 --> 11:23.481
Never forget that.

11:31.291 --> 11:33.992
(romantic music)

11:38.665 --> 11:43.301
♪ I'm not trading life
to be lonely tonight ♪

11:43.403 --> 11:44.202
- babe.

11:45.539 --> 11:46.705
It's our song.

11:51.044 --> 11:53.344
♪ so I cling to ♪

11:53.447 --> 11:56.881
♪ a speck of hope ♪

11:56.983 --> 11:59.284
♪ hope that you'll see me ♪

11:59.386 --> 12:02.353
♪ please, oh please ♪

12:14.668 --> 12:15.467
- daddy.

12:16.603 --> 12:19.137
Did you get mommy
more flowers again?

12:19.239 --> 12:20.605
- I sure did.

12:20.707 --> 12:21.506
You know why?

12:21.608 --> 12:22.674
- No.

12:22.776 --> 12:24.743
- Because she's
my little flower.

12:24.845 --> 12:27.846
(girl giggles)
(woman giggles)

12:27.948 --> 12:29.748
I refilled your prescription
at the hospital.

12:29.850 --> 12:30.882
- Thank you.

12:33.620 --> 12:35.019
Kayla, if you're finished,

12:35.122 --> 12:37.255
you can go ahead and play
for an hour before bed.

12:37.357 --> 12:38.056
(girl gasps)

12:38.158 --> 12:39.023
- okay.

12:42.362 --> 12:43.361
- Oh.

12:45.298 --> 12:47.332
- The realtor called.

12:47.434 --> 12:49.067
Your mother's house sold.

12:49.169 --> 12:50.068
She wants to know
what you wanna do

12:50.170 --> 12:51.770
with the rest of her belongings.

12:51.872 --> 12:52.637
- She's dead.

12:52.739 --> 12:54.105
Just throw it away.

12:54.207 --> 12:57.442
Don't need any
reminders of that drunk.

12:59.679 --> 13:01.546
Did you work today?

13:01.648 --> 13:02.680
- Yeah, from home.

13:02.783 --> 13:03.515
- You know, I think
it's a good idea

13:03.617 --> 13:05.283
if you make a habit of that.

13:05.385 --> 13:06.718
- Ed, I'm expected
to be at the office

13:06.820 --> 13:08.386
at least a few days a week.

13:08.488 --> 13:10.889
(utensils clang)

13:10.991 --> 13:12.090
- then quite your job.

13:12.192 --> 13:13.191
I mean it jade.

13:13.293 --> 13:14.058
- I can't.

13:14.161 --> 13:15.627
I'm in the middle of a project.

13:15.729 --> 13:18.563
- Your team will
pick up the slack.

13:19.733 --> 13:22.400
(phone vibrates)

13:23.503 --> 13:24.669
it's hospital.

13:26.239 --> 13:27.105
(ed sighs)

13:27.207 --> 13:28.373
I've gotta go.

13:30.677 --> 13:31.843
Don't wait up.

13:44.057 --> 13:46.791
(dishes bang)

13:46.893 --> 13:49.327
(light music)

14:03.743 --> 14:06.344
(kayla sniffing)

14:09.716 --> 14:11.749
- baby, did you
have a bad dream?

14:11.852 --> 14:12.917
- [kayla] no.

14:14.387 --> 14:16.855
- [jade] well
then, what's wrong?

14:16.957 --> 14:19.591
- I'm crying because
you do, mommy.

14:19.693 --> 14:21.192
- When do I cry?

14:21.294 --> 14:23.194
- [kayla] all the time.

14:30.103 --> 14:32.871
- [ed] have you
given your notice?

14:34.307 --> 14:35.139
- No.

14:40.180 --> 14:42.146
- We discussed this, all right?

14:42.249 --> 14:43.281
Get it done.

14:50.690 --> 14:53.258
I'll be home after dinner.

14:53.560 --> 14:55.126
Okay?

14:55.228 --> 14:57.061
(intriguing music)

14:57.163 --> 15:06.871
♪♪

15:35.268 --> 15:36.267
- hey sweetie.

15:36.369 --> 15:37.402
- Hi.

15:37.504 --> 15:38.703
- Enjoying your breakfast?

15:38.805 --> 15:39.504
- Yes.

15:39.606 --> 15:40.471
- Good.

15:40.573 --> 15:43.074
(intriguing music)

15:48.481 --> 15:51.482
(door unlocks)

15:51.584 --> 15:53.217
- babe, I left my cellphone.

15:53.320 --> 15:55.019
Is it in the kitchen?

15:57.357 --> 15:58.790
- [jade] I don't see it.

15:58.892 --> 16:01.859
(suspenseful music)

16:06.666 --> 16:08.266
- it's right there.

16:12.339 --> 16:13.838
Bye doctor kayla!

16:13.940 --> 16:15.473
- [kayla] bye daddy!

16:15.575 --> 16:16.441
- See ya.

16:23.183 --> 16:25.483
- Okay sweetie, we gotta go.

16:26.453 --> 16:28.720
Look, we'll get you donuts.

16:36.963 --> 16:37.795
(jade sighs)

16:37.897 --> 16:38.596
- hey.

16:38.698 --> 16:39.597
- [jade] hey.

16:39.699 --> 16:41.065
- Did you find everything?

16:41.167 --> 16:42.333
- Yeah.

16:42.435 --> 16:43.501
I put kayla to sleep
in the guest room.

16:43.603 --> 16:44.502
Thank you.

16:44.604 --> 16:46.070
- Is she okay?

16:46.172 --> 16:47.538
- Yeah.

16:47.640 --> 16:49.941
She doesn't really
understand what's going on,

16:50.043 --> 16:54.645
but it's better to be here
than somewhere strange.

16:54.748 --> 16:56.247
- I'm here for you.

16:57.150 --> 16:58.182
Both of you.

16:59.786 --> 17:03.087
I won't bail on you
like I did last time.

17:05.291 --> 17:06.157
Sisters?

17:09.696 --> 17:10.561
- Sisters.

17:13.233 --> 17:13.998
- Okay!

17:14.100 --> 17:15.400
(women laugh)

17:15.502 --> 17:17.769
enough of this mushy stuff.

17:17.871 --> 17:18.803
You hungry?

17:20.840 --> 17:23.141
(dog barking in distance)
- jade?

17:23.243 --> 17:24.108
Home!

17:32.519 --> 17:33.384
Jade!

17:43.396 --> 17:44.595
(ed sighs)

17:44.697 --> 17:47.632
(suspenseful music)

18:11.424 --> 18:16.327
(phone rings)
(suspenseful music)

18:22.368 --> 18:32.043
(phone ringing)

18:32.145 --> 18:40.785
(phone ringing)

18:40.887 --> 18:43.521
(ed grunts)

18:43.623 --> 18:45.623
(phone rings)

18:45.725 --> 18:47.792
(ed yells)

18:47.894 --> 18:50.495
(dramatic music)

18:50.597 --> 19:00.238
♪♪

19:00.340 --> 19:08.012
♪♪

19:11.618 --> 19:14.485
♪ I need deliverance ♪

19:15.588 --> 19:19.790
♪ if you want to,
come and set me free ♪

19:20.560 --> 19:24.962
♪ there's no forgiveness ♪

19:25.965 --> 19:29.500
♪ for the way
you're touching me ♪

19:34.807 --> 19:37.508
(elevator rings)

19:41.314 --> 19:42.480
- when did you
start working out?

19:42.582 --> 19:43.981
- [jade] three years ago.

19:44.083 --> 19:46.384
Why are you here again, ed?

19:46.486 --> 19:48.186
- Wanted to bring you these.

19:48.288 --> 19:49.754
Brighten your day.

19:51.224 --> 19:52.323
Where's kayla?

19:52.425 --> 19:56.060
- [jade] leigh's picking
her up after school.

19:57.163 --> 19:59.363
- What does your sister
think about all this?

19:59.465 --> 20:03.367
- If you're wondering if I
told her anything, don't worry.

20:03.469 --> 20:05.937
- What is there to tell, jade?

20:07.941 --> 20:10.374
You broke up our family
and I'm worried about you.

20:10.476 --> 20:12.143
- We're fine.

20:12.245 --> 20:13.978
- You're not fine, jade.

20:14.080 --> 20:16.047
Depression doesn't go away.

20:16.149 --> 20:17.848
I remember how low you were
after your parent's accident.

20:17.951 --> 20:19.483
I think your sister
coming back has

20:19.586 --> 20:21.118
stirred that all up again.

20:21.221 --> 20:24.488
Just come home so I can
help you like I always have.

20:24.591 --> 20:25.890
Please, just come home.

20:25.992 --> 20:26.891
- Sorry to interrupt.

20:26.993 --> 20:29.360
Jade, the clients are here.

20:29.462 --> 20:30.962
- Thank you, liam.

20:32.065 --> 20:35.499
I'll see you Friday,
when you pick kayla up.

20:37.870 --> 20:40.671
(suspenseful music)

20:40.773 --> 20:42.106
- [jade] thank you.

20:48.715 --> 20:51.382
(upbeat music)

20:51.484 --> 20:53.784
(cheering)

20:54.887 --> 20:56.020
(whistle blows)

20:56.122 --> 20:58.289
(cheering)

21:03.463 --> 21:04.328
- hi.

21:05.698 --> 21:07.565
- Can't believe you two
are calling it quits.

21:07.667 --> 21:09.233
- Yeah.

21:09.335 --> 21:12.203
- [shawn] I mean I've been there
since the beginning, you know?

21:12.305 --> 21:14.372
Best man at your wedding.

21:14.474 --> 21:15.873
- Yeah, I know.

21:15.975 --> 21:19.343
I'm still trying to get my
head around it, if I'm honest.

21:19.445 --> 21:22.146
Jade's obviously going
through something.

21:22.248 --> 21:22.913
- [coach] nice, nice!

21:23.016 --> 21:24.415
- [parent] good job.

21:24.517 --> 21:25.583
- Well, I'm not telling
wendy you're on the market

21:25.685 --> 21:27.285
'cause she'd leave me
in a red hot minute.

21:27.387 --> 21:28.085
(ed laughs)

21:28.187 --> 21:28.886
- come on.

21:28.988 --> 21:29.754
Settle down.

21:29.856 --> 21:31.188
You run this town.

21:31.291 --> 21:32.990
- True, but you saved her
with that triple bypass,

21:33.092 --> 21:36.494
so I think you got one
up on me, you know?

21:41.534 --> 21:44.168
(whistle blows)

21:45.071 --> 21:45.970
- go kayla!

21:48.274 --> 21:49.674
Good job, good job!

21:49.776 --> 21:50.641
Good try!

21:52.378 --> 21:55.479
- That was an incredible
pitch you just nailed.

21:55.581 --> 21:57.315
I mean, we haven't
been able to land that

21:57.417 --> 22:00.518
client in years and then
boom, you just do it.

22:00.620 --> 22:02.186
- I think I just had
a good read on them.

22:02.288 --> 22:03.721
(jade giggles)
- nah.

22:03.823 --> 22:07.124
You always know what the client
wants, even before they do.

22:07.226 --> 22:08.826
It's amazing, really.

22:08.928 --> 22:10.428
- Thank you, liam.

22:11.164 --> 22:12.229
All right, I should
probably get going.

22:12.332 --> 22:13.164
I'm already late.

22:13.266 --> 22:13.931
But I will see you tomorrow.

22:14.033 --> 22:15.599
- That you will.

22:15.702 --> 22:16.567
Goodnight jade.

22:16.669 --> 22:17.835
- Goodnight.

22:17.937 --> 22:18.636
Hey leigh.

22:18.738 --> 22:19.670
I'm sorry.

22:19.772 --> 22:21.605
My meeting ran over.

22:21.708 --> 22:24.041
Yeah, but I'm on my way now.

22:25.111 --> 22:25.976
Thank you.

22:35.922 --> 22:37.788
(suspenseful music)

22:37.890 --> 22:40.224
ed, what are you doing here?

22:40.326 --> 22:41.726
- Here go your papers.

22:41.828 --> 22:42.993
- Yeah, we'll they're
pretty straightforward.

22:43.096 --> 22:45.262
I don't want anything, so.

22:45.365 --> 22:46.731
- And you think I'm
gonna sign them so what,

22:46.833 --> 22:50.101
you can screw that leech
liam with a clear conscience?

22:50.203 --> 22:51.035
- Let go.

22:53.639 --> 22:55.072
Let go or I'll file
a restraining order

22:55.174 --> 22:57.375
and how would that look?

22:57.477 --> 22:58.876
- Go ahead and try, jade.

22:58.978 --> 23:00.111
No one's gonna believe you.

23:00.213 --> 23:01.979
I save lives, remember.

23:02.081 --> 23:04.982
And everyone thinks you're
crazy and you should be with me.

23:05.084 --> 23:07.885
- I'd rather die
than be with you.

23:12.525 --> 23:14.425
- And I'd rather cut you
up in a million little ways

23:14.527 --> 23:17.328
than let anyone else
have a piece of you.

23:17.430 --> 23:20.398
(suspenseful music)

23:22.402 --> 23:23.768
(engine starts)

23:29.442 --> 23:32.076
(tires screech)

23:38.651 --> 23:40.518
- [leigh] oh my god.

23:40.620 --> 23:42.586
I'm so happy you got
into this house.

23:42.688 --> 23:43.354
- I know.

23:43.456 --> 23:44.555
I'm so lucky.

23:45.925 --> 23:48.893
All right, I think that that
is the last of the gifts.

23:48.995 --> 23:51.662
- [leigh] yeah.
- Mommy, when is daddy coming?

23:51.764 --> 23:53.597
- Well, you and your
daddy get to celebrate

23:53.699 --> 23:56.834
your birthday again
this weekend together.

23:56.936 --> 23:58.135
- Okay.

23:58.237 --> 24:00.104
- All right, now why don't
you take this upstairs

24:00.206 --> 24:02.206
and you can play with that.

24:02.308 --> 24:04.475
And me and auntie leigh
are gonna clean up.

24:04.577 --> 24:05.443
- Yes.

24:05.545 --> 24:06.744
- And put your pajamas on.

24:06.846 --> 24:08.179
- [kayla] okay.

24:09.081 --> 24:10.781
(jade sighs)

24:10.883 --> 24:14.785
- so, what does ed think
about your new place?

24:14.887 --> 24:16.620
- He actually hasn't
said anything yet.

24:16.722 --> 24:18.689
- Well, did he sign the papers?

24:18.791 --> 24:21.492
- My lawyer got them back today.

24:21.594 --> 24:22.460
- Wow.

24:23.696 --> 24:25.362
So that's it, huh?

24:25.465 --> 24:26.330
- Yeah.

24:32.138 --> 24:35.105
(suspenseful music)

24:49.755 --> 24:51.655
(tires screech engine roars)

24:55.261 --> 24:58.996
(suspensful music)

25:08.875 --> 25:10.241
- all right.

25:10.343 --> 25:12.476
Go warm-up with the team.

25:13.379 --> 25:14.612
I'll be right there!

25:22.488 --> 25:23.354
- Hey.

25:25.258 --> 25:27.091
This is diana.

25:27.193 --> 25:27.858
Jade.

25:27.960 --> 25:29.059
- It's nice to meet you.

25:29.161 --> 25:30.494
My oldest plays in
the same league.

25:30.596 --> 25:32.863
- Well, it's a good league.

25:35.001 --> 25:36.133
- I should go talk to the coach.

25:36.235 --> 25:38.235
- Yeah.
- I'll see you.

25:41.574 --> 25:42.907
- Girlfriend?

25:43.009 --> 25:45.342
- We've been out a few times.

25:45.444 --> 25:46.844
Shawn introduced us.

25:46.946 --> 25:48.679
She's great.

25:48.781 --> 25:50.381
Hey, have a come by the
house and pick up your stuff.

25:50.483 --> 25:51.215
- Oh no.

25:51.317 --> 25:52.182
I'm good.

25:53.786 --> 25:55.152
- Well, look, unfortunately,

25:55.254 --> 25:57.054
I'm gonna be away for a
conference for a few days,

25:57.156 --> 25:58.989
so I won't be able to take
kayla for my weekend.

25:59.091 --> 26:00.124
- It's okay.

26:01.527 --> 26:05.262
- Can I come and grab her for a
few hours on the way back?

26:05.364 --> 26:06.797
Take care.

26:06.899 --> 26:07.765
- You too.

26:15.474 --> 26:16.440
- Hmm.

26:19.378 --> 26:20.811
See you guys next week.

26:20.913 --> 26:21.779
Bye.

26:33.726 --> 26:36.694
(suspenseful music)

26:40.266 --> 26:41.065
- jade!

26:44.971 --> 26:45.836
Hey!

26:48.374 --> 26:49.239
Hey.

26:50.076 --> 26:51.642
I'm glad I caught you.

26:51.744 --> 26:56.146
I wanted to ask you earlier,
but you were so busy.

26:56.248 --> 26:59.883
Did you want to maybe get
together this weekend?

26:59.986 --> 27:01.218
- Grab a drink or some food?
- What?

27:01.320 --> 27:02.653
- No!

27:02.755 --> 27:03.587
- Oh.

27:04.357 --> 27:05.222
Okay.

27:06.292 --> 27:08.993
See you in the office on Monday.

27:09.095 --> 27:11.662
(tense music)

27:21.407 --> 27:24.375
(suspenseful music)

27:25.144 --> 27:26.010
- leigh!

27:29.348 --> 27:30.214
Leigh!

27:32.752 --> 27:33.550
Kayla!

27:44.263 --> 27:46.730
(phone rings)

27:47.633 --> 27:48.499
- jade.

27:48.601 --> 27:49.833
- Where is she?

27:49.935 --> 27:51.201
- Jade, what are
you talking about?

27:51.303 --> 27:54.304
(phone beeps)

27:54.407 --> 27:55.973
hello, jade?

27:56.075 --> 27:57.741
Jade, are you there?

28:00.546 --> 28:02.613
Jade, is kayla okay?

28:02.715 --> 28:03.914
- She's fine.

28:04.016 --> 28:05.349
- Look, jade, I don't
know what's going on,

28:05.451 --> 28:06.517
but I've just arrived
in phoenix.

28:06.619 --> 28:07.317
I've gotta go.

28:07.420 --> 28:10.154
(dramatic music)

28:14.193 --> 28:16.994
(intense dramatic music)

28:17.096 --> 28:26.870
♪♪

28:29.542 --> 28:30.240
- jade, hey.

28:30.342 --> 28:31.141
- [jade] hey.

28:31.243 --> 28:32.409
- What are you doing here?

28:32.511 --> 28:35.612
- I was gonna check
in on something.

28:35.715 --> 28:37.448
- Oh, well can I help?

28:37.550 --> 28:38.582
I am the boss.

28:41.120 --> 28:42.453
- Right.

28:42.555 --> 28:45.556
- By the way, I was really
sorry to hear about you and ed.

28:45.658 --> 28:48.459
Wendy and I, the four of
us never really hung out,

28:48.561 --> 28:52.029
but I know ed so.

28:52.131 --> 28:54.465
So who knows, maybe you can
find a way to work it out.

28:54.567 --> 28:55.432
He's good people.

28:56.502 --> 28:59.002
- You know I was gonna ask

28:59.105 --> 29:02.406
about something with the
school zoning matter.

29:02.508 --> 29:04.007
It's fine, I can just
have the board follow up.

29:04.110 --> 29:05.142
- [officer] are you sure?

29:05.244 --> 29:06.243
I can help.
- Yeah, thank you.

29:06.345 --> 29:07.377
No, no, no, it's
good, it's good.

29:07.480 --> 29:10.013
- Okay, see you later.

29:10.116 --> 29:10.981
- See ya.

29:12.218 --> 29:13.250
- Bye.

29:13.352 --> 29:15.953
(ominous music)

29:22.261 --> 29:24.027
- why didn't you say anything?

29:25.164 --> 29:26.363
- I didn't tell anybody.

29:28.400 --> 29:29.066
- [leigh] I should have saw it.

29:29.168 --> 29:30.100
I should've saw it.

29:30.202 --> 29:33.103
- No, nobody saw it, nobody.

29:34.406 --> 29:37.141
Everyone thinks
ed walks on water

29:37.910 --> 29:39.443
but he was good to me.

29:39.545 --> 29:42.346
He was there for me when
mom and dad died and then

29:46.585 --> 29:48.318
one day, we were
at a friend's house

29:50.289 --> 29:51.488
and I corrected
him on something,

29:51.590 --> 29:53.023
I can't even remember what.

29:56.428 --> 29:57.294
And when we got home

30:01.100 --> 30:02.132
that was the first time.

30:02.234 --> 30:03.801
And I rationalized it.

30:03.903 --> 30:05.068
You know, I rationalized it

30:05.171 --> 30:06.870
to his mother always
cutting him down

30:06.972 --> 30:11.575
but after that it was like

30:11.677 --> 30:13.911
everything I did.

30:15.381 --> 30:16.180
- Jade.

30:18.717 --> 30:20.250
I'm so sorry.

30:22.655 --> 30:26.256
And I swear

30:26.358 --> 30:27.691
I will never

30:27.793 --> 30:30.160
let him hurt you again.

30:32.064 --> 30:33.263
- I don't think you can.

30:41.607 --> 30:43.140
I think he's trying to kill me.

30:43.242 --> 30:44.041
- What?

30:45.044 --> 30:46.210
Jade, no, if that's the case,

30:46.312 --> 30:48.145
you have no choice but
to go to the police.

30:48.247 --> 30:50.280
- His best friend is
the police sergeant.

30:51.183 --> 30:52.015
And I know ed.

30:53.252 --> 30:54.518
He'll turn it around.

30:54.620 --> 30:56.119
He'll make me seem
like I'm the crazy one.

30:56.222 --> 30:57.754
She's the one who had
the nervous breakdown,

30:57.857 --> 30:59.923
another one he had to save.

31:02.695 --> 31:04.695
The only way anyone
would believe it

31:04.797 --> 31:06.330
is if it came from
his own mouth.

31:10.102 --> 31:12.569
- Then what are you gonna do?

31:15.007 --> 31:16.173
- I don't know.

31:16.275 --> 31:18.742
(dark music)

31:31.056 --> 31:32.990
- (remembering conversation) the
only way anyone would believe it

31:33.092 --> 31:35.959
is if it came out
of his own mouth.

31:37.229 --> 31:39.096
- [leigh] what are you gonna do?

31:39.198 --> 31:41.098
What are you gonna do?

31:41.200 --> 31:43.934
(ominous music)

31:53.846 --> 31:58.582
- so I packed you both
lunches to eat at the park.

31:59.551 --> 32:01.618
- Can we get ice cream?

32:01.720 --> 32:03.053
- Yeah, of course, sweetie.

32:04.156 --> 32:07.424
- Jade, I don't think
you should be alone.

32:07.526 --> 32:08.926
I think you should go
with us to the park

32:09.028 --> 32:11.194
and we can figure out a plan
for you to get out of here.

32:11.297 --> 32:12.629
We can do it-

32:12.731 --> 32:15.065
- kay baby, why don't
you go get your jacket

32:15.167 --> 32:16.566
to go to the park?

32:17.403 --> 32:19.236
That is beautiful sweetie.

32:19.338 --> 32:20.337
- Thank you.

32:25.077 --> 32:27.577
- I don't want you
to worry, okay.

32:30.049 --> 32:31.581
But if something does happen,

32:31.684 --> 32:33.183
I need to know that you're
gonna look after kay.

32:33.285 --> 32:35.686
- Jade, I am not okay with that.

32:35.788 --> 32:38.522
- Please, will you
just promise me?

32:41.560 --> 32:42.459
Trust me.

32:46.932 --> 32:47.831
- All right.

32:50.602 --> 32:51.601
- All right.

32:53.238 --> 32:56.540
Okay sweetie, are you
ready to go to the park?

32:56.642 --> 32:57.808
- Yeah.

32:57.910 --> 32:59.810
- Okay, now listen
to mommy all right.

32:59.912 --> 33:01.044
- [kay] okay.

33:01.146 --> 33:02.813
- I want you to be a good girl.

33:02.915 --> 33:03.981
- [kay] okay.

33:04.083 --> 33:05.315
- And I want you to
listen to auntie lee.

33:05.417 --> 33:06.883
- [kay] okay.

33:06.986 --> 33:09.820
- And I want you to remember
that mommy loves you so much.

33:09.922 --> 33:11.388
- I love you too, mommy.

33:11.490 --> 33:14.124
(gentle music)

33:16.895 --> 33:18.428
- all right kiddo, you ready?

33:18.530 --> 33:19.229
- [kay] yeah.

33:19.331 --> 33:20.030
- All right, let's go.

33:20.132 --> 33:21.164
Hey,

33:21.266 --> 33:22.933
be careful.

33:23.402 --> 33:26.470
All right, kiddo, let's do it.

33:26.572 --> 33:28.939
(ominous music)

33:29.041 --> 33:30.741
(audience clapping)

33:30.843 --> 33:31.908
- thank you.

33:32.011 --> 33:36.513
After performing 1,248
lifesaving surgeries

33:37.616 --> 33:39.816
I still believe I can do better.

33:39.918 --> 33:41.918
In fact, we all can.

33:43.288 --> 33:45.455
And with what I will share
today, I hope we will.

33:45.557 --> 33:48.158
(ominous music)

33:54.666 --> 33:55.999
most of us in this room

33:56.101 --> 33:57.934
have devoted our lives to
cardiothoracic surgery.

33:58.037 --> 33:59.436
So I don't have to tell you

33:59.538 --> 34:02.239
that work-life balance has
not been high on our agendas.

34:03.242 --> 34:04.107
Thank god for my wife.

34:04.209 --> 34:05.842
Thank god for my wife.

34:05.944 --> 34:06.710
Thank god for my wife.

34:06.812 --> 34:09.546
(ominous music)

34:11.050 --> 34:12.382
we've been tasked
with supporting

34:12.484 --> 34:14.951
the most vulnerable cases

34:15.054 --> 34:16.753
and it is my hope and desire

34:16.855 --> 34:19.990
(dramatic music)
(items clanking)

34:20.092 --> 34:22.459
with are skills and dedication,

34:22.561 --> 34:25.495
we never have to lose another
patient on the or table again.

34:26.999 --> 34:27.998
Thank you.

34:28.100 --> 34:30.834
(dramatic music)

34:30.936 --> 34:33.136
- stupendous ed, I don't know
what more to say.

34:33.238 --> 34:34.371
1,248?

34:34.473 --> 34:35.338
- And counting.

34:35.441 --> 34:37.474
- Don't be so modest.
(chuckles)

34:37.576 --> 34:42.412
(ominous music)
(jade grunting)

34:59.164 --> 35:01.631
(dog barking)

35:18.217 --> 35:19.116
- jade?

35:21.487 --> 35:22.352
Jade?

35:26.792 --> 35:27.657
Oh my god.

35:30.028 --> 35:32.963
(mysterious music)

35:35.767 --> 35:37.934
- [dispatcher] 911,
what's your emergency?

35:38.036 --> 35:39.202
- It's my wife.

35:39.304 --> 35:41.538
She's gone and everything's-

35:42.875 --> 35:44.040
- [dispatcher] sir?

35:44.143 --> 35:46.143
Sir, can you explain
to me what's happening?

35:46.245 --> 35:48.245
- I don't know what's happened

35:48.347 --> 35:50.714
but there's blood everywhere

35:51.617 --> 35:54.117
and she's not here.

35:56.655 --> 35:57.921
She's not here.

35:58.857 --> 36:00.390
My wife's not here.

36:00.492 --> 36:01.858
- [dipatcher] sending
someone out right away.

36:01.960 --> 36:02.993
- Okay, what do you
want for dinner?

36:03.095 --> 36:04.928
You think like macaroni
and cheese, maybe?

36:05.030 --> 36:07.364
- Yeah, macaroni and cheese.

36:07.466 --> 36:11.101
Daddy!
- Hey, hey dr. Kayla.

36:11.203 --> 36:12.536
How are you?

36:12.638 --> 36:13.537
- Good, daddy.
- Good, good.

36:13.639 --> 36:15.105
- What's going on?

36:15.207 --> 36:16.173
Where's jade?

36:16.275 --> 36:17.274
- I don't know.

36:17.376 --> 36:18.074
- What do you mean?

36:18.177 --> 36:19.543
- Look, there's no time.

36:20.946 --> 36:22.579
The police are gonna be in
touch and I'll call you later.

36:22.681 --> 36:23.580
- You son of a bitch.

36:23.682 --> 36:25.515
- Lee, stop!
- Where is my sister?

36:25.617 --> 36:27.317
- Not now okay, please.

36:27.419 --> 36:28.952
This is hard enough
for everyone.

36:30.622 --> 36:31.388
I'll be in touch.

36:31.490 --> 36:32.622
Come on, baby,

36:32.724 --> 36:34.291
you're gonna stay
with daddy tonight.

36:39.264 --> 36:41.865
- [jade] hi, this is jade.

36:41.967 --> 36:44.601
(ominous music)

37:08.093 --> 37:10.760
(phone ringing)

37:15.500 --> 37:16.233
- yeah?

37:16.335 --> 37:17.500
- It's me.

37:17.603 --> 37:18.335
The cops are still there
but it looks legitimate.

37:18.437 --> 37:20.570
I don't care what you do

37:20.672 --> 37:23.940
just get rid of the
body and we're done.

37:24.910 --> 37:27.510
(ominous music)

37:48.667 --> 37:52.335
(jade grunting)
(items clanking)

37:52.437 --> 37:57.307
(ominous music)
(jade grunting)

38:12.691 --> 38:15.392
(ominous music)

38:22.234 --> 38:28.138
(car alarm ringing
in the distance)

38:28.240 --> 38:31.041
(mysterious music)

38:31.143 --> 38:40.850
♪♪

38:42.354 --> 38:46.323
- nobody would believe
what you tried to do to me

38:48.694 --> 38:50.927
so I'm gonna make sure
you tell them yourself.

38:51.797 --> 38:54.431
(ominous music)

39:02.274 --> 39:04.874
(phone dinging)

39:12.651 --> 39:14.784
- [ed] how does
it feel to be mrs. Thompson?

39:14.886 --> 39:15.719
- Perfect.

39:17.055 --> 39:18.154
Got my perfect flowers.

39:19.157 --> 39:22.058
(doorbell ringing)

39:25.964 --> 39:28.865
- [ed] detectives,
have you found her?

39:29.801 --> 39:30.567
- Not yet.

39:31.636 --> 39:32.502
Can we come in?

39:32.604 --> 39:33.403
- Of course.

39:34.539 --> 39:35.739
Come right through here.

39:42.180 --> 39:44.781
- You said jade has a
history of depression?

39:44.883 --> 39:46.349
- Yeah, she does.

39:48.086 --> 39:49.786
It started after
her parents died.

39:50.856 --> 39:52.956
I helped her get
it under control

39:53.058 --> 39:57.160
but about a month ago, I
noticed her spiraling again.

39:57.262 --> 39:58.862
- What about the abuse?

39:58.964 --> 40:01.464
- Jade doesn't drink
or use any other drugs.

40:01.566 --> 40:02.932
We don't even
alcohol in the house.

40:03.034 --> 40:04.701
- The physical abuse?

40:04.803 --> 40:05.869
- I'm sorry, I don't follow.

40:05.971 --> 40:07.370
- Jade's sister came
into the station.

40:07.472 --> 40:09.105
She told use jade
recently confided

40:09.207 --> 40:11.374
that you'd been abusive
during your marriage.

40:11.476 --> 40:13.343
In fact, she said jade thought

40:13.445 --> 40:15.211
you were trying to
have her killed.

40:16.214 --> 40:19.149
(ominous music)

40:19.251 --> 40:20.617
- I'm sorry.

40:20.719 --> 40:22.285
I don't know where lee
would've gotten that from,

40:22.387 --> 40:24.821
but you're aware she's
bipolar, aren't you?

40:26.024 --> 40:28.191
And a drug problem.

40:28.293 --> 40:31.294
I mean she disappeared for 10
years living on the streets.

40:31.396 --> 40:33.563
She didn't tell you any of this?

40:33.665 --> 40:35.432
- No, no she didn't.

40:36.568 --> 40:39.569
- Lee has some really
shady people around.

40:41.239 --> 40:42.672
She even claimed she
was being followed.

40:42.774 --> 40:45.442
Now I don't know if that was
in her head or if it was real

40:45.544 --> 40:48.711
but now she's telling these
stories about me, why?

40:50.549 --> 40:53.082
Because I have my
reservations about her?

40:54.419 --> 40:59.088
You tell me detective, as
a father and a husband,

40:59.624 --> 41:00.056
wouldn't you?

41:02.961 --> 41:04.861
- Well, thank you dr. Thompson.

41:04.963 --> 41:07.030
You've given us some
leads we can follow.

41:08.500 --> 41:09.399
- Thank you.

41:10.469 --> 41:14.070
Detectives, what do
I tell my daughter?

41:15.474 --> 41:16.673
- I would tell her the truth,

41:16.775 --> 41:18.241
that you don't know
where her mother is.

41:20.145 --> 41:21.711
- Thank you.

41:21.813 --> 41:24.514
(ominous music)

41:32.724 --> 41:33.790
- [ed] there's my wife.

41:33.892 --> 41:36.092
How does it feel to
be mrs. Thompson?

41:36.194 --> 41:36.993
- [jade] perfect.

41:38.296 --> 41:39.762
Got my perfect flowers

41:40.599 --> 41:42.765
and got my perfect man.

41:44.603 --> 41:46.135
That's all I need.

41:46.238 --> 41:49.939
- [ed] well from now on
you are my top flower.

41:52.878 --> 41:53.943
I love you.

41:54.045 --> 41:55.478
- I love you too.

41:58.049 --> 41:58.882
We got married.

41:58.984 --> 42:01.551
(ed chuckling)

42:02.721 --> 42:05.121
(dark music)

42:15.767 --> 42:17.233
- [reporter on television]
throttled the canucks 9-2

42:17.335 --> 42:20.470
and the oilers needed overtime
to beat the rangers one zip.

42:20.572 --> 42:22.438
- [reporter 2] good morning,
let's talk about the weather.

42:22.541 --> 42:27.911
Las vegas 68, los angeles 72
with a high of 82,

42:28.013 --> 42:32.482
georgia 56 degrees
with a high of 71.

42:32.584 --> 42:35.418
- [reporter 1] and now jen has
a local story.

42:35.520 --> 42:37.186
- [jen] jade thompson, a
local mother and wife

42:37.289 --> 42:39.422
has been missing since
yesterday morning

42:39.524 --> 42:40.924
when her estranged husband,

42:41.026 --> 42:43.359
when dr. Edward thompson
called police to her home.

42:43.461 --> 42:46.095
So far detectives on the case
have given very little clues

42:46.197 --> 42:47.897
as to what may have occurred

42:47.999 --> 42:49.132
other than to say

42:49.234 --> 42:51.568
her disappearance is
considered suspicious.

42:52.170 --> 42:56.773
We'll be right back after these
messages.

42:56.875 --> 43:09.586
- If it has to be clean.

43:09.688 --> 43:12.422
(ominous music)

43:40.051 --> 43:41.985
(dramatic music)

43:42.087 --> 43:44.754
(phone ringing)

43:52.764 --> 43:53.563
- dr. Thompson.

43:54.532 --> 43:55.431
- [female] this is alouette,

43:55.533 --> 43:56.866
calling just to confirm
your reservation

43:56.968 --> 43:58.668
tonight for two
at eight o'clock.

43:58.770 --> 43:59.602
- There must be some mistake,

43:59.704 --> 44:00.903
I didn't make a reservation.

44:01.006 --> 44:02.672
- [female] it was made
under a jade thompson.

44:02.774 --> 44:03.773
Shall I confirm it?

44:05.543 --> 44:06.342
Hello?

44:12.250 --> 44:14.384
(ominous music)

44:14.486 --> 44:17.587
(rain pattering)

44:17.689 --> 44:24.594
♪♪

44:33.705 --> 44:34.671
(car horn beeps)

44:38.643 --> 44:41.444
(ominous music)

44:41.546 --> 44:51.187
♪♪

44:51.289 --> 45:00.897
♪♪

45:00.999 --> 45:10.606
♪♪

45:10.709 --> 45:20.316
♪♪

45:20.418 --> 45:30.059
♪♪

45:30.161 --> 45:39.936
♪♪

45:53.952 --> 45:56.119
- [don] I got the cash
and her body's dealt with

45:56.221 --> 45:57.553
so now we're done.

45:57.655 --> 46:00.256
(ominous music)

46:06.731 --> 46:07.964
- [ed] hello.

46:08.066 --> 46:10.833
Apparently there's a
reservation under thompson.

46:10.935 --> 46:12.969
- [receptionist] here we
are, for two, right this way.

46:13.071 --> 46:14.437
- Sorry, I don't suppose

46:14.539 --> 46:16.005
you know when the
reservation was made, do you?

46:16.107 --> 46:17.807
- Sorry sir, we don't
keep a record of that

46:17.909 --> 46:19.742
but a card did
arrive for your table

46:19.844 --> 46:21.611
so if you'll just follow me.

46:29.554 --> 46:32.421
A server will be right
over with the wine list,

46:32.524 --> 46:34.023
but the chef has
already been instructed

46:34.125 --> 46:36.592
to prepare you and your
wife's anniversary dish,

46:36.694 --> 46:38.694
the chateaubriand.

46:38.797 --> 46:39.595
Enjoy.

46:44.803 --> 46:47.370
(ominous music)

47:20.805 --> 47:23.539
(woman laughing)

47:25.977 --> 47:28.611
(ominous music)

47:28.713 --> 47:38.421
♪♪

47:59.510 --> 48:02.144
- [don] I got the cash
and the body's dealt with.

48:02.247 --> 48:03.312
So now we're done.

48:20.198 --> 48:23.132
(knocking on door)

48:26.037 --> 48:27.870
- what the hell do you want?

48:27.972 --> 48:28.871
- I need to talk
to you about jade.

48:28.973 --> 48:30.172
- Why?

48:30.275 --> 48:31.340
So you can tell
me a bunch of lies

48:31.442 --> 48:33.242
like you did the police

48:33.344 --> 48:35.511
about what a drug addict
and a crazy bitch I am?

48:35.613 --> 48:36.412
I don't think so.

48:39.150 --> 48:40.016
- Look,

48:42.086 --> 48:45.154
she made a dinner reservation
for us for our anniversary.

48:46.791 --> 48:51.627
I just need to know did she
do that before to reconcile?

48:52.130 --> 48:53.095
- Seriously?

48:54.132 --> 48:55.598
You tried to kill her ed,

48:55.700 --> 48:56.999
so trust me

48:57.101 --> 48:58.701
she wasn't planning on
celebrating your anniversary.

48:58.803 --> 48:59.969
And let me tell you something,

49:00.071 --> 49:01.837
if anything has happened to her,

49:03.274 --> 49:04.974
I'll kill you myself.

49:05.076 --> 49:07.677
(ominous music)

49:24.862 --> 49:27.029
- [don] I got the cash and
the body is dealt with.

49:27.832 --> 49:29.332
So now we're done.

49:29.434 --> 49:31.934
(ominous music)

49:32.036 --> 49:41.644
♪♪

49:41.746 --> 49:42.445
♪♪

49:42.547 --> 49:43.512
(door slams shut)

50:58.322 --> 51:00.890
(gentle music)

51:04.328 --> 51:08.264
(thunder rumbles)

51:31.122 --> 51:32.788
- what are you doing, sweetie?

51:32.890 --> 51:34.423
No, no, no, no,
not in the street.

51:35.960 --> 51:37.326
Get out of the street, baby.

51:48.406 --> 51:51.207
Kayla, where are you going?

51:51.309 --> 51:54.143
(mysterious music)

51:54.245 --> 52:03.986
♪♪

52:15.166 --> 52:15.865
where are you?

52:15.967 --> 52:18.134
Where are you, kayla?

52:18.236 --> 52:21.003
(thunder clapping)

52:22.473 --> 52:23.339
- kayla!

52:26.978 --> 52:28.644
Kayla, where are you?

52:31.215 --> 52:32.248
Kayla baby?

52:34.418 --> 52:35.251
Kayla?

52:36.721 --> 52:39.989
Ah, come on, we've got to
get to your new babysitter's.

52:40.091 --> 52:40.856
- [kayla] daddy, I saw a rabbit.

52:40.958 --> 52:42.091
- [ed] you did?

52:42.193 --> 52:43.692
Okay, well maybe you can
tell kelly all about it

52:43.794 --> 52:45.494
when we get there, okay?

52:45.596 --> 52:48.197
(ominous music)

52:59.177 --> 53:00.142
(gate clangs)

53:05.483 --> 53:06.515
(keys jingle)

53:15.760 --> 53:18.961
(computer starting up)

53:22.700 --> 53:23.666
(computer chirps)

53:26.270 --> 53:29.171
(computer chirps)

53:55.166 --> 53:57.633
(ominous music)

53:57.735 --> 54:07.509
♪♪

54:12.149 --> 54:14.650
- in four hours, some of
you will be assisting me

54:14.752 --> 54:17.253
with what will be your
first transcatheter surgery.

54:17.355 --> 54:19.288
So it's important we
go over the procedure.

54:19.390 --> 54:21.824
We want to be prepared
for every eventuality.

54:22.960 --> 54:23.959
In the first slide,

54:24.061 --> 54:25.928
you'll see the aortic
valve in question.

54:28.633 --> 54:33.435
Now this is where we'll
be placing the catheter.

54:35.439 --> 54:37.439
The second slide
shows the placement-

54:37.541 --> 54:40.009
(ominous music)

54:40.111 --> 54:41.210
- I'm sorry, this is.

54:42.079 --> 54:44.713
(ominous music)

55:03.501 --> 55:04.366
- dr. Thompson?

55:06.203 --> 55:07.603
- Get out.

55:07.705 --> 55:11.006
(tense piano music)

55:11.108 --> 55:12.441
I said, "get out"!

55:12.543 --> 55:15.444
(tense piano music)

55:20.785 --> 55:23.385
(ominous music)
(thunder rumbling)

55:38.936 --> 55:40.002
- [don] this is
don's cell phone.

55:40.104 --> 55:42.071
Leave a message or don't.

55:42.173 --> 55:45.207
(gentle ominous music)

55:45.309 --> 55:54.917
♪♪

55:55.019 --> 56:04.626
♪♪

56:04.729 --> 56:14.370
♪♪

56:14.472 --> 56:24.079
♪♪

56:24.181 --> 56:26.615
♪♪

56:26.717 --> 56:29.118
(thunder rumbling)

56:31.822 --> 56:33.822
(banging on door)

56:35.092 --> 56:37.126
- why don't you answer
your god damn phone?

56:37.228 --> 56:38.093
- We were done.

56:39.296 --> 56:41.397
- No, 'cause I want to
know if you did the job.

56:42.733 --> 56:46.001
- You saw it, the cops saw it.

56:46.103 --> 56:48.804
- Then why the hell does it
feel like she's still alive?

56:50.508 --> 56:52.207
I just want to know,

56:52.309 --> 56:54.109
I just want some
proof, that's all.

56:54.211 --> 56:57.045
Show me that you did what
you said you were gonna do.

57:05.723 --> 57:06.955
- Is that the proof
you're looking for?

57:10.561 --> 57:11.827
- She never took this off.

57:11.929 --> 57:12.895
- I told you I did the job

57:12.997 --> 57:14.296
just like I got paid to.

57:15.366 --> 57:17.766
So whatever's going on,

57:18.035 --> 57:19.668
it's your deal.

57:19.770 --> 57:22.438
(ominous music)

57:24.041 --> 57:25.107
(door slams)

57:25.209 --> 57:27.676
(thunder rumbles)

57:27.778 --> 57:30.612
(ominous music)

57:30.714 --> 57:40.055
♪♪

57:40.157 --> 57:41.890
(glass clanking)

57:41.992 --> 57:44.593
